Meanwhile, journalist Richard Hall, who is based in Paris, reminds his 6,800
followers:

> Last time Israel invaded Gaza 1,387 Palestinians were killed. 773 were
> civilians, including 320 children and 109 women. (Source: B'Tselem)
>
> — Richard Hall (@_RichardHall) [July 17,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/_RichardHall/statuses/489865183360458752)

Today is the 11th day of the start of “Operation Defensive Edge,” which has
left more than 230 Palestinians dead, including women and children, and more
than 1,500 injured.

From Gaza, Hamas, which has ruled the strip since 2007, has [fired
missiles](http://www.washingtonpost.com/world/israel-launches-major-operation-
against-hamas-in-gaza-
strip/2014/07/08/81874d52-067a-11e4-a0dd-f2b22a257353_story.html) into Israel.
Most of the rockets coming into Israel have caused no serious damage, due in
part to the US-funded Iron Dome aerial defense system, [which has intercepted
at least 70 projectiles so
far,](http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/jul/11/israeli-air-strikes-gaza-
continue-us-barack-obama-offers-broker-ceasefire) according to the Guardian.

With the group operations, the casualties are expected to rise.

